40|$|The {{objective}} of this thesis {{is to find out}} on the example of the core countries of the Euro area - France and Germany, if a <b>single</b> european <b>currency</b> is a sufficient assumption for economic stability of the selected countries and of the Euro area. The theoretical part outlines historical consequences of the creation of a <b>single</b> european <b>currency</b> and the roles of France and Germany in the European integration. The practical section contains an analysis of impacts of introducing the <b>single</b> european <b>currency.</b> Particular impacts of the adoption of common currency are assessed on inflation, on inhabitants, on international business with France and Germany and on economic growth...|$|R
